ubezogenen Museumslandschaft in Deutschland suchen.  aFor the first time, the publication reveals the full dimensions of the material remembrance culture devoted to coal mining. It focuses on the museum as preserver of an objective heritage and on the objects themselves. Individual studies on technological innovations are juxtaposed against survey presentations about the museumization of coal mining. The volume is completed by a comprehensive overview of museums and collections in Germany.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCoal mines and miningxMuseumszGermany. 4aBergbaugeschichte. 4aMusealisierung. 4amaterial culture. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh1 aFarrenkopf, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrenkopf, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGanzelewski, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeide, Anna-Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrzigoda, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRazum, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiemer, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiemer, Stefan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVossenkuhl, Maren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWerner, Claus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is pa